    <div class="content"><p>GPUs work with polygons, have alpha channels and much more.   They can do complex translations and 3-D mappings.   Though basic GPU function in the display is probably something that happens over time, the function I describe is way below what GPUs do today.   It&#8217;s more like the bitblt terminal from Bell Labs 30 years ago.</p>
